short_description_of_the_course.value:
The aims of the course are to: 
Introduce students to modern software development methods and techniques for building and maintaining large systems;
Prepare students to apply these methods and techniques presented to them in the context of an extended group-based software development exercise;
Make the students aware of the professional, social and ethical dimensions of software development; 
Instil in the students a professional attitude towards software development.

course_aims.value:
The aims of the course are to: 
Introduce students to modern software development methods and techniques for building and maintaining large systems;
Prepare students to apply these methods and techniques presented to them in the context of an extended group-based software development exercise (Team Project (H)); 
Make the students aware of the professional, social and ethical dimensions of software development; 
Instil in the students a professional attitude towards software development.
Develop students’ understanding of sustainability and decarbonisation as related to the topic.

intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of this course students will be able to:
Identify the main phases of software development and how they are related in contemporary development methods;
Maintain an existing medium to large-scale system according to supplied requirements (this will include modifying some of the system documentation);
Identify and discuss critically professional, social, environmental and ethical issues involved in large-scale software development;
Plan, organise and schedule a substantial team based project;
Capture and specify functional and non-functional requirements;
Design, specify; implement and test a system which demonstrably meets project requirements;
Maintain appropriate, clear and accurate documentation;
Use appropriate QA techniques, including test suite planning;
Use appropriate configuration management tools and techniques;
Deliver articulate and informative presentations on project topics;
Communicate effectively within the project team;
Work successfully within a team.
